{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:54:17,067", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:54:17.067330\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement a parser for the job description to extract key requirements and skills\", \"result\": \"```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Analyze the job description to extract key requirements and skills\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume to identify relevant experience and qualifications\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate technical interview questions based on job requirements and candidate's resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview and record candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses based on predefined criteria\\\",\\n    \\\"Send automated emails for interview scheduling and follow-up\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation repor...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n- The output is only a list of workflow steps, not a parser implementation.\\n- It does not meet the requirement to “implement a parser for the job description to extract key requirements and skills.”\\n- The required output format is Python code that performs the parsing, not just a list of strings.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\nfrom typing import List\\n\\ndef parse_job_description(job_desc: str) -> List[str]:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Parse the job description text to extract key requirements and skills.\\n    Returns a list of extracted items.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    requirements = []\\n\\n    # Split into lines and look for common bullet markers\\n    for line in job_desc.splitlines():\\n        line = line.strip()\\n        if not line:\\n            continue\\n        # Bullet points\\n        if line.startswith((\\\"-\\\", \\\"*\\\")):\\n            item = line.lstrip(\\\"-* \\\").strip()\\n            if item:\\n                requirements.append(item)\\n        else:\\n            # Look for sentences starting with keywords\\n            match = re.match(r\\\"^(?:Required|Must have|Preferred|Experience with|Proficiency in)[:\\\\s]*(.+)$\\\", line, re.IGNORECASE)\\n            if match:\\n                # Split comma-separated skills\\n                parts = [part.strip() for part in match.group(1).split(\\\",\\\") if part.strip()]\\n                requirements.extend(parts)\\n\\n    # Deduplicate while preserving order\\n    seen = set()\\n    unique_requirements = []\\n    for req in requirements:\\n        if req.lower() not in seen:\\n            seen.add(req.lower())\\n            unique_requirements.append(req)\\n\\n    return unique_requirements\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    jd_text = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    We are looking for a Software Engineer who meets the following criteria:\\n    - 5+ years of Python development experience\\n    - Experience with Django and Flask frameworks\\n    - Proficiency in RESTful API design\\n    * Strong knowledge of SQL and NoSQL databases\\n    Must have: Docker, Kubernetes, and AWS\\n    Preferred: Familiarity with CI/CD tools like Jenkins or GitLab CI\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    extracted = parse_job_description(jd_text)\\n    print(extracted)\\n```\"}"}
